name: mmlCache
description: 1.1.0-pl A generic caching snippet for caching the output of any MODx Element using a configurable cache handler.

cacheElementKey.name: cacheElementKey
cacheElementKey.desc: An optional explicit key to use to cache the output. Otherwise, the key is uniquely generated based on the Resource it is executing on, the properties being passed to the Element, and the $_REQUEST parameters passed when it executed.
cacheElementKey.desc_trans: An optional explicit key to use to cache the output. Otherwise, the key is uniquely generated based on the Resource it is executing on, the properties being passed to the Element, and the $_REQUEST parameters passed when it executed.

cacheExpires.name: cacheExpires
cacheExpires.desc: How many seconds the output of the Element is to be cached by getPage; 0 means indefinitely or until the cache items are purposely cleared.
cacheExpires.desc_trans: How many seconds the output of the Element is to be cached by getPage; 0 means indefinitely or until the cache items are purposely cleared.

cacheHandler.name: cacheHandler
cacheHandler.desc: The class of cache handler for getCache to use.
cacheHandler.desc_trans: The class of cache handler for getCache to use.

cacheKey.name: cacheKey
cacheKey.desc: The key identifying a cache handler for getCache to use.
cacheKey.desc_trans: The key identifying a cache handler for getCache to use.

element.name: element
element.desc: The name of a MODx Element that will be called by the getCache snippet instance.
element.desc_trans: The name of a MODx Element that will be called by the getCache snippet instance.

elementClass.name: elementClass
elementClass.desc: The class of the MODx Element that will be called by the getCache snippet instance.
elementClass.desc_trans: The class of the MODx Element that will be called by the getCache snippet instance.

namespace.name: namespace
namespace.desc: An execution namespace that serves as a prefix for placeholders set by a specific instance of the getCache snippet.
namespace.desc_trans: An execution namespace that serves as a prefix for placeholders set by a specific instance of the getCache snippet.

toPlaceholder.name: toPlaceholder
toPlaceholder.desc: The name of a placeholder the Element being called is setting it's output into. This allows getCache to support Snippets that do not directly return their output.
toPlaceholder.desc_trans: The name of a placeholder the Element being called is setting it's output into. This allows getCache to support Snippets that do not directly return their output.
